The Senate on Tuesday considered a total of three bills including the bills seeking to establish the National Industrial Technology Park; the Federal College of Agriculture Ise-Orin, Ekiti State; and the Federal University of Agriculture Ogoja, Cross River State. The three bills were sponsored by Senators Ibikunle Amosun (Ogun Central), Biodun Olujimi (Ekiti South) and Agom Jarigbe (Cross River North). After consideration the Bills were referred by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, to the Committees on Trade and Investment; and the Joint Committees on Tertiary Institutions and Agriculture and Rural Development. The Committees have four weeks to report back to the full chamber.